<article class="comment-article com-show" id="tree_47471699" data-cid="47471699">
    <div id="comment_47471699">
        <header data-points="5" data-reason="Funny">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Fieldwork in particular?"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Fieldwork in particular?<span> (5, Funny)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~Krishnoid" class="author" title="author name and user ID">Krishnoid (984597) </a> | about a week ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=5414347&cid=47471699">(#47471699)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_47471699" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="5" data-reason="Funny">
            <div class="comment-body"><p><div class="quote"><p>SKINNER: Six hours, nineteen minutes, right ascension, fourteen degrees, twenty-two minutes declination... no sighting.</p><p>BART: Mm-hm.</p><p>SKINNER: Six hours, nineteen minutes, right ascension, fourteen degrees, twenty-three minutes declination... no sighting.</p><p>BART: Mm-hm.</p><p><nobr> <wbr></nobr>...</p><p>SKINNER: (excitedly) Six hours, nineteen minutes, right ascension, fourteen degrees, fifty-eight minutes declination!<nobr> <wbr></nobr>...no sighting. Did you get that one Bart?</p><p>BART: Hell no.</p></div><p>I can't imagine why scientific fieldwork in particular could provide an environment that promotes inappropriate behavior.</p></div>
